        −
        1
        )
        .
      
    
    {\displaystyle R\left[f^{-1}\right]=R[t]/(tf-1).}
  )The localization is frequently applied to a commutative ring R with respect to the complement of a prime ideal (or a union of prime ideals) in R. In that case 
  
    
      
        S
        =
        R
        −
        
          
